            <div class="col-md-8">
                <h3><b>Name: Yiming Huan</b></h3>
                <h4><b>Education Background:</b> Master's degree (Piano Performance)</h4>
                <h4><b>Research Area:</b> Piano teaching and research</h4>
                <br />
                <p>Ms. Yiming Huan began to play the piano at the age of 5. She gave her first performance at the age of eight, and her first concert at the age of thirteen. 
                    Her main teachers were Ms. Meige Li and Mr. Zhebang Xie, the chairman and vice chairman of the Shanghai musicians' association's piano committee, respectively. 
                    She obtained her bachelor's degree in music at the Nanjing University of Arts in 2010, achieving an average grade above 90%. 
                    In 2014, she attended the MMus program at the University of Alberta, in Canada, where she is currently a Master Candidate under the supervision of Professor Jacques Després. 
                    Before commencing her Masters course, Ms. Huan also received education training and taught piano, along with solfeggio and ear training, at the University of Taizhou.</p>

                <p>
                    Ms. Huan has won many honors: the Top 100 Excellent Guide Teacher Award of China; the Gold award in the Piano specialist division of the Shanghai International Music Competition; 
                    received the “Outstanding Teacher” award from the “Concerned about the next generation committee” of the State Council; the winner of the Gold award in a concerto festival held by Nanjing municipal committee; 
                    awarded with gold in the instrumental division of higher education teachers in Taizhou; wrote and published the essay “Music Cultural Relativity” in Chinese core journals.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Ms. Huan was also employed as the music adviser for the Yangtze River Group and Chunlan group. Both groups were amongst the top 500 enterprises in China. Due to having a managerial and leadership role, her position often consisted of planning and organizing events. 
                    During the same period, Ms. Huan kept herself busy by also being employed as a guest performer for the Women’s Orchestra of Jiangsu province. Apart from these involvements, she is a distinguished performer in China of the piano brand “Bentley”.
                </p>

                <p>
                    In 2014, Ms. Huan commenced her Master of performance in piano at the University of Alberta. She got the first prize in “Kiwanis Music Festival” both in “Multi Movement” and “Romantic” group.
                     She also became a member of the “Golden Key International Honour Society”, and obtained the Beryl Barns scholarship，the Queen Elizabeth II scholarship and the Graduate Student Scholarship from Government of Alberta. 
                    She performed in many concerts, some of which have recordings that can be found on CKUA Radio and Youtube.
                </p>
